  3. EFFECT OF FLIPPING sigma_i ON S_hat(k)

    For chord i (gap g=i+1), flipping sigma_i changes S_hat(k) by:
    Delta(k) = omega^{-kg} - omega^{kg} = -2i*sin(2*pi*k*g/p)

    chord 0 (g=1):  k=1: 0.000-1.564j  k=2: 0.000-1.950j  k=3: 0.000-0.868j
    chord 1 (g=2):  k=1: 0.000-1.950j  k=2: 0.000+0.868j  k=3: -0.000+1.564j
    chord 2 (g=3):  k=1: 0.000-0.868j  k=2: -0.000+1.564j  k=3: 0.000-1.950j

